Silene coronaria is a herbaceous plant commonly known as Rose Campion. 
It is a biennial or perennial plant that grows up to 2 feet in height. 
The plant has soft, hairy leaves that are grayish-green in color. 
The flowers of Silene coronaria are magenta or pink in color and have an elegant, star-shaped appearance. 
The petals are fringed, and each bloom grows on a long, slender stalk. 
Silene coronaria is commonly found in gardens, as it bears attractive flowers and has a long blooming season. 
The plant is also used in landscaping as an ornamental plant, thanks to its showy appearance and easy maintenance.
